{
  "texts": [
    "Globally, he is interested in climate change and is particularly focused on monitoring and mitigating a range of extreme phenomena to contribute towards fostering a sustainable environment.G.",
    "Kermarrec is a Post-Doctoral researcher currently with the Institute for meteorology and climatology at the Leibniz University in Hanover (Germany).",
    "Her research interests include correlation analysis of various geodetic sensors (Terrestrial Laser Scanner or GNSS) but also surface modelling of point clouds and deformation analysis.",
    "Her main field of interest is the physical modeling of atmospheric correlations based on the turbulence theory using real observations and LES.",
    "E. Forootan is a Professor of Geodesy and Earth Observation at Aalborg University (Denmark)."
  ]
}